<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i> and/or <i>Viguiera</i> <i>parishii</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Agave</i> <i>deserti</i>, <i>Ambrosia</i> <i>dumosa</i>, <i>Ambrosia</i> <i>salsola</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Bebbia</i> <i>juncea</i>, <i>Coleogyne</i> <i>ramosissima</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>acanthocarpa</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>echinocarpa</i>, <i>Encelia</i> <i>farinosa</i>, <i>Ephedra</i> <i>nevadensis</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>laricifolia</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>linearifolia</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>teretifolia</i>, <i>Ferocactus</i> <i>cylindraceus</i>, <i>Gutierrezia</i> <i>microcephala</i>, <i>Krameria</i> <i>grayi</i>, <i>Larrea</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Prunus</i> <i>fremontii</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>ovata</i>, <i>Salazaria</i> <i>mexicana</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>dorrii</i>, <i>Simmondsia</i> <i>chinensis</i>, <i>Stephanomeria</i> <i>pauciflora</i> and <i>Yucca</i> <i>schidigera</i>. Emergent trees or tall shrubs may be present at low cover, including <i>Fouquieria</i> <i>splendens</i>, <i>Juniperus</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Juniperus</i> <i>osteosperma</i>, <i>Senegalia</i> <i>greggii</i> or <i>Yucca</i> <i>brevifolia</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 2 m; canopy is open to intermittent open. Herbaceous layer is open to intermittent with seasonal annuals. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Eriogonum fasciculatum</i> > 2% absolute cover or > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy; other shrubs, if present, < half its cover, but <i>Hyptis emoryi</i> or <i>Salvia dorrii</i> may be higher (Thomas et al. 2004).</li>
		
		<li><i>Eriogonum fasciculatum</i> > 5% absolute cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998b).</li>
		
		<li><i>Viguiera parishii</i> ≥ any other species in absolute cover in the shrub canopy; emergent <i>Juniperus californica, Rhus ovata</i> or other tall shrub ≤ 5% in absolute cover (Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998b, Evens and San 2005).</li>
		
		<li><i>Viguiera parishii</i> ≥ 2% absolute cover and other shrubs = or < cover in the shrub canopy (Thomas et al. 2004).</li>
		
		<li><i>Eriogonum fasciculatum</i> or <i>Viguiera parishii</i> > 30% relative cover in the shrub canopy, except if co-dominant with <i>Yucca schidigera </i>(Evens et al. 2014).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Wash and arroyo margins, rocky to bouldery alluvium, canyons and moderate to steep colluvial slopes and ridges. Soils are well drained and derived from granitic or volcanic rock.  </div>
</div>

        
